When creating or editing Next.js components:

- Use Tailwind CSS with LeadPulse colors (e.g., `bg-marigold`, `text-muted-sky-blue`).
- Integrate Magic UI components for animations:
  - Glowing Button for CTAs (e.g., `<button className="magic-glow bg-marigold">Verify Lead</button>`).
  - 3D Card Tilt for dashboard widgets (e.g., `<div className="magic-3d-card bg-warm-ivory">{content}</div>`).
- Follow component structure:
  ```jsx
  import { motion } from 'framer-motion';
  import { MagicGlow } from 'magic-ui';

  export default function ComponentName() {
    return (
      <div className="bg-warm-ivory">
        <motion.button
          className="magic-glow bg-marigold text-bright-white"
          whileHover={{ scale: 1.05 }}
        >
          Action
        </motion.button>
      </div>
    );
  }
  ```
Test locally with vercel dev to ensure animations and responsiveness.
Deploy to a preview URL (vercel) to verify in a browser.
Use admin account (admin@leadpulse.com) to test component functionality (e.g., lead upload form).
